examples.en: She sipped some lukewarm coffee from her mug.
He sipped on the bottle of water.
He sipped at his wine with pleasure.
I politely sipped my tepid coffee.
She sipped her wine, savouring every drop.
She sipped her drink with obvious pleasure.
Mathew picked up the cup and sipped his coffee.
He sipped leisurely at his drink.
She sipped her lemonade through a straw.
We sipped wine to the strains of Beethoven.

Ermyn didn't take sugar, but she sipped the nauseous solution bravely, incapable of rebuffing a kindness.
